name: Rice fields
address: Banjar Gagah, Tegallalang, Kec. Tegallalang, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80561, Indonesia
review 1: Beautiful place to have a quiet walk. Very few tourists around
review 2: One of Bali's last secrets. Not touched by  overtourism. Come early in the morning, and you might see five volcanoes on the horizon.
review 3: Tranquil fields, nice place for a walk or playing with a kite.
review 4: Always nice to enjoy and to take pictures in the beautiful rice fieds
review 5: The rice fields of Central-Bali are amazing. Definitely visit one of the many locations with rice fields.
